{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdb6-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"339"},"text":"§ 339.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Prevention and response workforces","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdb7-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Career Paths","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, acting through the Commandant, shall ensure that appropriate career paths for civilian and military Coast Guard personnel who wish to pursue career paths in prevention or response positions are identified in terms of the education, training, experience, and assignments necessary for career progression of civilians and members of the Armed Forces to the most senior prevention or response positions, as appropriate. The Secretary shall make available published information on such career paths.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdb8-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Qualifications for Certain Assignments","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An officer, member, or civilian employee of the Coast Guard assigned as a—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdb9-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" marine inspector shall have the training, experience, and qualifications equivalent to that required for a similar position at a classification society recognized by the Secretary under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s3316"},"text":"section 3316 of title 46","children":[],"tail":" for the type of vessel, system, or equipment that is inspected;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdba-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" marine casualty investigator shall have the training, experience, and qualifications in investigation, marine casualty reconstruction, evidence collection and preservation, human factors, and documentation using best investigation practices by Federal and non-Federal entities;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdbb-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" marine safety engineer shall have knowledge, skill, and practical experience in—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdbc-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the construction and operation of commercial vessels;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdbd-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" judging the character, strength, stability, and safety qualities of such vessels and their equipment; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdbe-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the qualifications and training of vessel personnel;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdbf-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" waterways operations manager shall have knowledge, skill, and practical experience with respect to maritime transportation system management; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc0-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/b/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" port and facility safety and security specialist shall have knowledge, skill, and practical experience with respect to the safety, security, and environmental protection responsibilities associated with maritime ports and facilities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc1-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Apprenticeship Requirement To Qualify for Certain Careers","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Commandant may require an officer, member, or employee of the Coast Guard in training for a specialized prevention or response career path to serve an apprenticeship under the guidance of a qualified individual. However, an individual in training to become a marine inspector, marine casualty investigator, marine safety engineer, waterways operations manager, or port and facility safety and security specialist shall serve a minimum of one-year as an apprentice unless the Commandant authorizes a shorter period for certain qualifications.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc2-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Management Information System","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, acting through the Commandant, shall establish a management information system for the prevention and response workforces that shall provide, at a minimum, the following standardized information on individuals serving in those workforces:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc3-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Qualifications, assignment history, and tenure in assignments.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc4-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Promotion rates for military and civilian personnel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc5-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sector Chief of Prevention","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"There shall be in each Coast Guard sector a Chief of Prevention who shall be at least a Lieutenant Commander or civilian employee within the grade GS–13 of the General Schedule, and who shall be a—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc6-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" marine inspector, qualified to inspect vessels, vessel systems, and equipment commonly found in the sector; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc7-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" qualified marine casualty investigator, marine safety engineer, waterways operations manager, or port and facility safety and security specialist.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc8-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Signatories of Letter of Qualification for Certain Prevention Personnel","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Each individual signing a letter of qualification for marine safety personnel must hold a letter of qualification for the type being certified.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdc9-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s339/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Sector Chief of Response","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"There shall be in each Coast Guard sector a Chief of Response who shall be at least a Lieutenant Commander or civilian employee within the grade GS–13 of the General Schedule in each Coast Guard sector.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id568bfdca-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/281/tV/s521/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–281, title V, § 521(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/2953"},"text":"124 Stat. 2953","children":[],"tail":", § 57; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/281/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–281, title II","children":[],"tail":", §§ 203, 221(b)(1)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3024"},"text":"128 Stat. 3024","children":[],"tail":", 3038; renumbered § 312, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI/s104/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 104(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4196"},"text":"132 Stat. 4196","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dG/tLVXXXV"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. G, title LVXXXV","children":[],"tail":" [LXXXV], §§ 8504(a), 8505(a)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4747"},"text":"134 Stat. 4747","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 339, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXII/s7201/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXII, § 7201(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1675"},"text":"139 Stat. 1675","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id568bfdcb-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id568bfdcc-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id568bfdcd-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For redesignation of prior sections 350 to 500 not listed below as having been previously repealed or renumbered, see Table Showing Redesignations Made by Title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282","children":[],"tail":" preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 356, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/521"},"text":"63 Stat. 521","children":[],"tail":", related to retirement for disabilities incident to service, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-03/ch536/s36"},"text":"act Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 536, § 36","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/408"},"text":"64 Stat. 408","children":[],"tail":". See sections 1204 and 1376 of Title 10, Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 358, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393/s1"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/522"},"text":"63 Stat. 522","children":[],"tail":", limited number of retirements in a calendar year of enlisted men who had completed 20 years of service, to not more than the whole number nearest 1 percent of the total enlisted force on the active list, and any men so authorized to be retired annually who were not so retired, could be retired during any subsequent year providing the total retired in that year did not exceed 3 percent of the total enlisted force, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/114/s1/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–114, § 1(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/144"},"text":"77 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior sections 363 and 364 were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-03/ch536/s36"},"text":"act Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 536, § 36","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/408"},"text":"64 Stat. 408","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 363, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/523"},"text":"63 Stat. 523","children":[],"tail":", related to retiring or dropping for disabilities not incident to service. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1207"},"text":"section 1207 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 364, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/523"},"text":"63 Stat. 523","children":[],"tail":", related to dropping for disabilities due to vicious habits. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1207"},"text":"section 1207 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 368, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/524"},"text":"63 Stat. 524","children":[],"tail":", related to discharge in case of under-age enlistment, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/322/tI/s115/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–322, title I, § 115(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1585"},"text":"96 Stat. 1585","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 425, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/525"},"text":"63 Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":", related to retiring boards, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-03/ch536/s36"},"text":"act Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 536, § 36","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/408"},"text":"64 Stat. 408","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1216"},"text":"section 1216 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior sections 431, 433, and 434 were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/640/s10/a/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–640, § 10(a)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3549"},"text":"100 Stat. 3549","children":[],"tail":", which provided in part that such repeal did not affect rights and duties that matured, penalties that were incurred, and proceedings that were begun under those sections before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1986","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 431, acts ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/526"},"text":"63 Stat. 526","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-03/ch536/s24"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 536, § 24","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/407"},"text":"64 Stat. 407","children":[],"tail":", related to personnel of former Life Saving Service."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 433, acts ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/528"},"text":"63 Stat. 528","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-09-27/ch586"},"text":"Sept. 27, 1949, ch. 586","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/698"},"text":"63 Stat. 698","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/130/s1/11"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(11)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/190"},"